{
  "texts": [
    "More recent is the adaptation of neuro/biofeedback scenarios in fully immersive contexts (Bossenbroek et al., 2020; Reddy & Lingaraju, 2020).",
    "Bossenbroek and colleagues (Bossenbroek et al., 2020) proposed an adaptation of the biofeedback-based game DEEP and tested it on young ADHD patients.",
    "The game is played in a fully immersive virtual environment (experienced by wearing an HTC VIVE (HTC, 2023a) and allows players to explore an underwater fantasy world using their breath to control movement.",
    "As far as the electroencephalographic signal is concerned, a recent work (although no tests have been conducted yet) is the one proposed in Reddy and Lingaraju (2020), in which neurofeedback (acquiring the neurosignal by means of a 14channel Emotiv Epoc) is returned in a mobile AR scenario (via smartphone).",
    "The idea is to allow the user to inflate a virtual balloon, or bend a virtual spoon while reaching the desired psychological state."
  ]
}